"n.防洪堤；隄岸 【英】 n. 防洪堤(an embankmen)；隄岸(bank of a river) 【考】 rampart : invasion / levee : flood(堡垒防止入侵/河堤 防止洪水)levee : river / cordon : crowd(河堤阻挡河流/警戒 线阻挡人群) 【记】 注意不要和lever(杠 杆)相混 n. (防止河流泛滥而建造的)防洪堤; 隄岸 【记】lev是""quot;升起""quot;的词根 【参】lever(n 杠杆; 控制杆; v 擡起); leverage(n 杠杆作用); levitate(v 使轻轻浮起) 【类】rampart: invasion = levee: flood = cordon: crowd = padding: damage堡垒防止入侵 = 河隄防止洪水 = 警戒线阻挡人群 = 填塞物防止损伤 【记】lev- 提高，升起, 比地平面高出一截的东西；level 水平，水平面，+ ee 对象，相关的物→levee是控制水平面的大堤 levee (n.1)  1719, ""natural or artificial embankment to prevent overflow of a river,"" from New Orleans French levée ""raising, lifting; embankment,"" from French, originally fem. past participle of lever ""to raise,"" from Latin levare ""to raise"" (see lever). levee (n.2)  ""morning assembly held by a prince or king (upon rising from bed),"" 1670s, from French lever ""a raising,"" noun use of verb meaning ""to raise"" (see levee (n.1))."
